"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody. I was reading some Albert Howard this morning. It's my little way of kind of pepping myself up to look at these two inspirational books that he wrote all about returning organic matter to the soil and how that will affect the health of everything that comes from that soil and how artificial manures, as he calls them, or fertilizers as we call them now, are a hindrance to the formation of a good biological churning of life in the soil, and that this is the essence of everything because it's this life that feeds the plants, and these healthy plants feed the animals, including ourselves. Everything is part of this system. And it occurred to me while I was reading it that Albert Howard failed. Of all the progress he made in showing what he showed throughout the entire world and influencing so many people to take up the indoor method of composting to revive the fields and all the fantastic results they had. At the end of the day, chemical fertilizing and conventional agriculture won out. And it's kind of a blow to my ego a little bit because I'm trying to change the world myself. I I want to tell people about these wonderful books. At the same time, I'm looking at it and saying, these great books are obscure and kind of hard to find and no one's heard of them. And Albert Howard really isn't that big a figure outside of my little world. How do I go about doing this? How how can I change the world if Albert couldn't? And it's it got me a little bit doubtful about what I'm trying to do and where I'm going. Some days are like that, and I have gloomy weather today, and it matches my gloomy spirit. So uh I'm trying to pull through it, reading my little book, make myself better and happier. But at the end of the day, I'm looking at it and saying the whole world is against this. This is something that all of agriculture is already committed to on the wrong side. How would I go about doing that if Albert Howard couldn't? Anyway, kind of a bum uh bummer video today, but I'm in a bummer mood. So I'd share uh my frustrations, my doubts, my my reservations that I can't change the world and maybe all this is just for nothing. But you know, I'm not doing anything better so I'm gonna keep on going and just keep on marching. And you know, I think the the old saying is when the good running back hits the pile he keeps his feet moving. So I'm gonna try to keep my feet moving. Anyway, thanks y'all\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody.\",\n      \"start\": 0.32,\n      \"end\": 1.76,\n      \"duration\": 1.44,\n      \"confidence\": 0.98,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 0.32,\n          \"end\": 0.56,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 0.975\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 0.56,\n          \"end\": 0.64,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 0.72,\n          \"end\": 0.96,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 0.96,\n          \"end\": 1.28,\n          \"duration\": 0.32,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ody\",\n          \"start\": 1.28,\n          \"end\": 1.52,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \".\",\n          \"start\": 1.52,\n          \"end\": 1.76,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 0.912\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"text\": \" I was reading some Albert Howard this morning.\",\n      \"start\": 1.76,\n      \"end\": 4.56,\n      \"duration\": 2.8,\n      \"confidence\": 0.997,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" I\",\n          \"start\": 1.76,\n          \"end\": 2.0,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n  